The article features various reactions to the nomination of Jim Yong Kim as President of the World Bank. Secretary of the Treasury Timothy F. Geithner praises Kim's qualifications and his commitment to development. Former President Bill Clinton commends Kim's leadership in health care and AIDS treatment. Rwandan President Paul Kagame describes Kim as a true friend of Africa who has supported the development of efficient health systems. Paul Farmer, a physician and colleague of Kim, highlights his three decades of dedication to breaking the cycle of poverty and disease. Jeffrey Sachs expresses his support for Kim's nomination via Twitter.